	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=6805&mid=10027606535045>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=6805&mid=10027606535045>RE: Int-class Tailors...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=6805&mid=10027606535045#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 10th 8:37 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=76404><span id= >Moraganth</span></a><br><span id=notbold>31 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Um, actually... <br><br>Strength as a secondary skill does NOT take place of intel or wisdom.&nbsp;&nbsp;As specifically stated by VI, a higher secondary skill will add a bonus to the ability to gain skill points/ succede making items, but a lower secondary skill will NOT decrease a persons chances.<br><br>A secondary skill only adds bonuses, it does not become the basis for the chances.  Go to EQTraders... learn it... live it... love it.  Your chances are either your intel OR wisdom, whichever is higher, plus any bonuses from a secondary skill.<br><br>"....if you have 100 INT, 76 WIS, and 214 STR..." your chance to skill up is based off your 100 INT, and then modified upwards with a bonus for your strength... assuming you're smithing.  VI has not said at which point bonuses start being added, but at 214 i'd imagine you'd be getting a decent bonus (i would hope, at least).<br><br>As for dex, originally it was said that Dex would be secondary for fletching, and with the advent of Boon of the Garou, people have found that the addition of 100 dex makes a difference for tailoring as well (see EQTraders forums).</p>&nbsp;<br>Moraganth<br><br>The most convincing arguement for the existance of intelligent life elsewhere in the universe is that they haven't made contact with us. </td></tr>
